    <!-- Origin Story -->
    <section class="section origin-section">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="origin-content">
          <div class="origin-text">
            <h2 class="section-title">How It All Began</h2>
            <div class="story-content">
              <p class="story-paragraph">
                In the digital corridors of Bengal College of Engineering and
                Technology, a group of passionate computer science students
                noticed a growing concern. As cyber threats evolved and
                multiplied, there was a significant gap between academic
                cybersecurity education and real-world application.
              </p>
              <p class="story-paragraph">
                Founded in 2021 by a dedicated team of final-year students,
                CyberCell BCET emerged from a simple yet powerful vision: to
                create a platform where students could not just learn about
                cybersecurity in theory, but actively engage with it, practice
                it, and contribute to the broader security community.
              </p>
              <p class="story-paragraph">
                What started as weekly meetups in a small classroom has now
                grown into one of the most active technical clubs of the
                college, with over 50+ active members.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="origin-visual">
            <div class="timeline-visual">
              <div class="timeline-line"></div>
              <div class="timeline-point active">
                <div class="point-year">2021</div>
                <div class="point-event">Club Founded</div>
                <div class="point-desc">
                  Started with 10 passionate students
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="timeline-point">
                <div class="point-year">2021</div>
                <div class="point-event">CTF Lab</div>
                <div class="point-desc">
                  Established dedicated CTF labs online for research and
                  learning purpose
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="timeline-point">
                <div class="point-year">2021</div>
                <div class="point-event">CTF Competition</div>
                <div class="point-desc">Organized our first CTF event.</div>
              </div>
              <div class="timeline-point">
                <div class="point-year">2022</div>
                <div class="point-event">First Seminar</div>
                <div class="point-desc">
                  Organized our first seminar over topic "Ethical Hacking and
                  SQL Injection"
